// Stdlib: FDM Effective-Property Correlations
//
// The β-phase of the v0.5 FDM-as-printed-FEA PRD
// (docs/prds/v0_5/fdm-as-printed-fea.md §"Built-in property correlations").
// Provides the human-facing citation + override surface for the
// effective-property correlation library that turns a base filament material
// plus FDM process parameters into the foundation's transverse-isotropic /
// orthotropic constitutive constants.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_5/fdm-as-printed-fea.md task β / slice 1.
//
// Module exports (added across the β TDD steps):
//   - `FDMCorrelationDefaults` — the default correlation constants
//     (build-Z knockdown ratios, Gibson-Ashby infill law (c, n), pattern
//     factors), each accompanied by a parallel
//     `..._provenance : MaterialPropertyProvenance` citation slot AND a
//     parallel `..._low_confidence : Bool` slot flagging defaults whose
//     evidence is weak (FDM-specific Gibson-Ashby exponent, directional
//     pattern factors).
//   - `FDMCouponOverride` — the user-facing coupon-override entry point;
//     optional user-measured elastic constants and infill-curve (c, n)
//     overrides that beat any default.
//
// Two-surface convention (see Plan §"Design Decisions"):
//   The same numeric defaults appear here (citation/override surface, read
//   by humans) AND as Rust `pub const`s in `crates/reify-fdm/src/correlation.rs`
//   (the compute source-of-truth that the δ-task ComputeNode calls directly).
//   Both sets are pinned by their own tests, so any divergence fails CI; the
//   two must move together. This mirrors the α/γ precedent where γ's
//   `ZoneProcessParams` re-declares `FDMProcess` defaults in Rust with a
//   "mirrors stdlib" comment.
//
// Per-property provenance + low-confidence convention:
//   Reuses `MaterialPropertyProvenance` from `std.materials.fea` (the
//   three-field citation record source / reference / notes) to annotate each
//   default. A parallel `..._low_confidence : Bool` slot makes
//   "low-confidence defaults flagged" (PRD §"Built-in property correlations")
//   a machine-checkable contract rather than buried prose.
//
// Cross-module dependencies (resolved via sequential-prelude in stdlib_loader):
//   - `MaterialPropertyProvenance` — from std.materials.fea
//   - `InfillPattern`              — from std.fdm
